This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as part-of-speech tagging and caption generation, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for captioning and multi-task learning for POS prediction and captioning also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves generating diverse and informative captions, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval tasks such as generating captions based on relationships between objects, which suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
